meanings.definition: Print (additional text or an image) on top of an existing print.
meanings.sent1: She carefully overprints her signature on the document.
meanings.sent2: The artist overprints the logo on the t-shirt.
meanings.sent3: The mischievous cat overprints its paw on the wet paint.
meanings.sent4: His laughter overprints the room, filling it with joy.
meanings.sent5: The storm overprints the landscape with its fierce presence.

meanings.definition: A printed mark or design that is added to a stamp after it has been printed.
meanings.sent1: The collector was excited to find a rare overprint on the stamp.
meanings.sent2: The overprint on the stamp made it unique.
meanings.sent3: The overprint on the stamp seemed to wink at the other stamps.
meanings.sent4: The overprint on the stamp was like a secret message waiting to be discovered.
meanings.sent5: The bright overprint on the stamp caught everyone's attention.
